exUEkPpR72poCdPEzc1J_DuHdoEQg-ikfriBv8t5kCoXMpqOGvfoBATOjMBzqGL3YZcsRfT0fFspdcPpzzab3wuk-yudxg5rSw4fUdChECwYEZoFfMKDhmkEqWw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating JUnit testing order**\\n\\nI’m considering using JUnit, where the class order is deterministic but not obvious, rather than alphabetical. Without a specified order, tests could run in discovery order based on classpath scanning. But then, what about the ordered jar entries in Gradle? The test task reads the classes directory, and that could potentially be sorted. Lastly, regarding code style, I might want to avoid comments in Java—markdown-style comments are not ideal.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.drbg.DRBG$6`.\n\nAdded:\n\n- `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/DRBGAnonymous6Test.java`\n\nWhat it covers:\n\n- Configures `org.bouncycastle.drbg.entropysource` through Bouncy Castle’s public DRBG configuration path.\n- Uses `SecureRandom.getInstance(\"DEFAULT\", provider)` and `SecureRandom.getInstance(\"NONCEANDIV\", provider)` to trigger DRBG initialization.\n- Supplies a public no-arg `EntropySourceProvider` implementation so `DRBG$6.run()` reaches `Class#newInstance()`.\n- Verifies the configured entropy provider was instantiated and used.\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction. Note: there were pre-existing unrelated modified files in the worktree, which I did not touch.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b44fd16b53ee99b0169fc43566b84819e880e9d73a105f191\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 880, "output": 1094, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32694, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778139974268, "responseId": "resp_0b44fd16b53ee99b0169fc4346f788819e9a003